This paper deals with recommending research articles to consumers of online vaccination information, which involves natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR) techniques. The paper uses Altmetric to select webpages related to vaccination and then tests a method for ranking research articles relative to each webpage using a canonical correlation analysis (CCA) approach. This involves analyzing the relationship between the webpage and the research articles to identify the most relevant ones. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.CY (Computers and Society), and cs.SD (Software Development and Programming Languages).
